@node "Whatis" "What is YAUU"
@{b}----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                Introduction
----------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Well YAUU (Yet Another Useless Utility) is basically a File requester. 
That's it.
But a File requester with ToolTypes! Why tooltypes? So it can but easily
configured to whatever @{b}You Need@{ub}

So why YAUU?
I found that people keep writing unarchivers and similar, but after a month
or more you always end up finding another archiving type, which of course 
is CLI only and lets face it, a pain in the arse.
So was born YAUU, This will only really be any use if you are lame like me 
and can't be bothered to type in CLI commands every 5 seconds.
I was going to write YAUU for uncompressing .adf only, but I know I will end 
up finding another Disk image type of program.

YAUU is only a front end file requester, by itself it cannot dearchive 
anything. YAUU is only meant for temporary use until your favourite 
programs support all the archivers you need.

YAUU doesn't claim to be able to do everything, so don't expect it to. I 
knocked this program up in about 30 minutes and I only required it for
.adf files, but did test it with an .lha aswell, it worked :)


YAUU is pre-configured to adf2disk filetype, but YAUU is fully configurable.
Please check out the examples for more information.

adf2disk, lha, lzx and dms are all freely available on the Aminet sites.
http://ftp.uni-paderborn.de/aminet/

Also check out the EMS homepage for updates to MADS and YAUU
http://www.agima.demon.co.uk/emailsoft/

@endnode

