@node "Usage" "How to Use YAUU"
@{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------
                            Usage & Requirements
------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
@{b}YAUU is WorkBench only, that's why it was written!@{ub}

@{b}Requirements@{ub}

An Amiga with OS 2.04+
and some thing to unarchive
Please feel free to tell me if you get this working on anything less 
than a 2.04 Amiga. (I assume ASL is 2.04+)?


@{b}Usage@{ub}

YAUU works by changing tooltypes values, if you don't know how to this 
then don't bother. YAUU also requires a basic understanding of CLI inputs
for Archiving programs i.e. DMS, LHA, LZX, etc....


@{b}The Tooltypes@{ub}

@{b} PROG=@{ub}     This is the dearchiving program you wish to use.

@{b} CMDLINE=@{ub}  Command Line, for setting the program to extract if this is
           required. if not leave blank, i.e. LHA requires e, adf2disk
           requires nothing to be entered. 

@{b} STADIR=@{ub}   The directory you would like YAUU to enter upon startup, 
           the default is "PROGDIR:". Which is where the program was
           initally started from.
 
@{b} DEFDIR=@{ub}   The default extract directory, please note this only 
           applies the programs such as LHA, LZX, etc NOT DMS types.
           If using with a disk image type program leave blank.

@{b} FTYPE=@{ub}    The filetype extension i.e. .lha .lzx .adf etc. This will
           place the requested string in the search pattern of the ASL
           requester.


@{b}Examples@{ub}

1) Lha Archive tooltype settings
       
       PROG=C:Lha
       CMDLINE= e 
       STADIR="Lha_Storage:"
       DEFDIR="Ram:"
       FTYPE=.lha


2) Amiga file to disk (afd2disk) tooltype settings
       
       PROG=C:adf2disk
       CMDLINE=
       STADIR="Work:adf/"
       DEFDIR=
       FTYPE=.adf


3) The DISK-Masher tooltype settings

       PROG=C:DMS
       CMDLINE= write
       STADIR="Work:DMS/"
       DEFDIR=
       FTYPE=.dms 


Only three examples, but should work with most other CLI style 
archiving programs. As long as they only have one command line
at the begining before the file name.
     
@endnode


@node "Bugs&Bombouts" "Bugger"
@{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------
                              Bugs & Bombs
------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

YAUU is very sensative to slight errors in the tooltypes, this doesn't
mean you'll bomb but it might have some interesting results.
Make sure you have followed the examples the Usage part of this guide.
Certain tooltypes require "" whilst others don't so please pay 
attention when entering.

@{b}KNOW BUGS
---------@{ub}

Important note: Do not rename YAUU to anything else, because it will no
longer be able to find it's tooltypes. You can check this by looking at
the top of the file requester. If the FTYPE isn't present at the top you
know it's not going to work. If it also appears that it has done nothing
i.e. clicked on a file to extract and the file requester appears almost
immediately afterwards there could be three reasons. 
 
 1) Your Amiga is too damn fast at extracting files
 2) There is an error in the tooltypes which mean that the program
    carries on regardless.
 3) User Error - Ain't nothing I can do about that.

Apart from that there are no real problems with YAUU. But I haven't 
tested it with many dearchiving programs, so your on your own, but hey 
what can go wrong?

         @{i} If you have any real problems then let me know.@{ui}

